    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Cordage fiber obtained from leaves of several plants from the genus Agave, especially Agave cantala, native to Mexico and introduced to the Philippines, Indonesia, and India. Maguey is woven into textile, rope, twine, and netting.</Note_Text>
